Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper presents a dataset and algorithm for semantic compositionality in written Dutch.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of a machine learning algorithm for extracting the types and derivations from the corpus.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and semantic compositionality, which are important topics in AI.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the complexity of the extraction algorithm and the types of lambda calculus used.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper presents an algorithm for extracting types and derivations from a corpus.
